summary: Spicy Chicken Ramen might be just the main course you are searching for. This dairy free recipe serves 4 and costs $3.12 per serving. One portion of this dish contains about 28g of protein, 18g of fat, and a total of 428 calories. Only a few people made this recipe, and 1 would say it hit the spot. Head to the store and pick up ramen eggs, chicken broth or, sambal oelek chili paste optional, and a few other things to make it today. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes approximately 40 minutes. It is brought to you by The Lemon Bowl. It is a rather expensive recipe for fans of Japanese food. Taking all factors into account, this recipe earns a spoonacular score of 0%, which is very bad (but still fixable). Similar recipes include 30 Minute Spicy Miso Chicken Katsu Ramen, 30 Minute Spicy Miso Chicken Katsu Ramen, and Spicy Ramen Cup of Noodles.

winePairing.pairingText: Riesling, Sake, and Sauvignon Blanc are my top picks for Ramen Noodles. Saké is an obvious choice when it comes to Japanese food. If you want to stick to grape wine, though, you might opt for sauvignon blanc or riesling. You could try Zilliken Rausch Riesling Spatlese. Reviewers quite like it with a 4.6 out of 5 star rating and a price of about 65 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Zilliken Rausch Riesling Spatlese
productMatches.description: Fruit driven finesse is marked with a delicate florality in this late-picked Riesling. Notes of vineyard peach, grapefruit, juicy lemon and ripe passion fruit come together on a creamy, concentrated palate rich with melon and candied lemon peel. Stunning exchange of racy acidity and layered sweetness together form a perfectly poised whole. The long, juicy finish and fantastic vintage hint at a beautiful future yet to come.

instructions:
Instructions

 

Pre-heat oven to 375. Brush chicken breasts with olive oil on both sides and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roast in oven until golden brown, about 20 minutes.

While chicken is roasting, begin heating sesame oil in a large soup-pot. Add ginger and chile paste and heat until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Stir in chicken broth, soy sauce, hoisin and rice vinegar plus a pinch of salt and pepper. Bring to a boil then reduce to simmer.

When chicken is cooked, remove from oven and let cool enough to handle. Use two forks or your fingers to shred chicken. Add shredded cooked chicken and mushrooms to the pot and return to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes.

Divide cooked ramen noodles between four bowls then ladel the chicken ramen on top of each. Garnish with optional toppings to serve.
